<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE of 8 November 1990 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to direct life assurance, laying down provisions to facilitate the effective exercise of freedom to provide services and amending Directive 79/267/EEC (90/619/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu direktiiv 90/619/EM&Uuml; otsese elukindlustusega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, millega n&auml;hakse ette s&auml;tted teenuste osutamise vabaduse tegeliku kasutamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks ja muudetakse direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml; 8. november 1990 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Articles 57 (2) and 66 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;iget 2 ja artiklit 66, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to develop the internal market in life assurance and in the operations referred to in First Council Directive 79/267/EEC of 5 March 1979 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking-up and pursuit of the business of direct life assurance (4), hereinafter called the "First Directive' as last amended by the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal; whereas, in order to achieve that objective, it is desirable to make it easier for assurance undertakings having their head office in the Community to provide services in the Member States, thus making it possible for policy-holders to have recourse not only to assurers established in their own country, but also to assurers which have their head office in the Community and are established in other Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vaja on arendada elukindlustuse ja nende tegevuste siseturgu, mida on k&auml;sitletud 5. m&auml;rtsi 1979. aasta esimeses n&otilde;ukogu direktiivis 79/267/EM&Uuml; otsese elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, (4) edaspidi "esimene direktiiv", viimati muudetud Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemisaktiga; selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks on soovitav muuta &uuml;henduses peakontorit omavatele elukindlustusseltsidele kergemaks teenuste osutamine liikmesriikides, v&otilde;imaldades seega kindlustusv&otilde;tjatel p&ouml;&ouml;rduda mitte ainult nende oma riigis asuvate kindlustajate, vaid ka kindlustajate poole, kelle peakontor on &uuml;henduses ja kes on asutatud teistes liikmesriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under the Treaty, any discrimination with regard to freedom to provide services based on the fact that an undertaking is not established in the Member State in which the services are provided has been prohibited since the end of the transitional period; whereas that prohibition applies to services provided from any establishment in the Community, whether it be the head office of an undertaking or an agency or branch; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt asutamislepingule on alates &uuml;leminekuperioodi l&otilde;pust teenuste osutamise vabaduse osas keelatud igasugune diskrimineerimine sel p&otilde;hjusel, et kindlustusselts ei ole asutatud liikmesriigis, kus teenuseid osutatakse; seda keeldu kohaldatakse iga &uuml;henduses asutatud kindlustusseltsi teenuste suhtes, olgu see kindlustusseltsi peakontor v&otilde;i esindus v&otilde;i filiaal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for practical reasons, it is desirable to define provision of services taking into account both the assurer's establishment and the place where the commitment is to be covered; whereas, therefore, commitment should also be defined; whereas, moreover, it is desirable to distinguish between activities pursued by way of establishment and activities pursued by way of freedom to provide services; </inglise>
<eesti> praktilistel p&otilde;hjustel on soovitav m&auml;&auml;ratleda teenuste osutamine, v&otilde;ttes arvesse nii kindlustaja asukohta kui kohustuse t&auml;itmise kohta; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks samuti m&auml;&auml;ratleda kohustus; lisaks on soovitav eristada asutamisel p&otilde;hinevat tegevust teenuste osutamise vabadusel p&otilde;hinevatest tegevustest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is desirable to supplement the First Council Directive in order in particular to clarify the powers and means of supervision vested in the supervisory authorities; whereas it is also desirable to lay down specific provisions regarding the taking-up, pursuit and supervision of activity by way of freedom to provide services; </inglise>
<eesti> soovitav on t&auml;iendada esimest n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi eriti j&auml;relevalveasutustele antud j&auml;relevalvevolituste ja -vahendite t&auml;psustamiseks; lisaks on soovitav n&auml;ha ette eris&auml;tted, mis k&auml;sitlevad teenuste osutamise vabadusel p&otilde;hineva tegevuse alustamist, j&auml;tkamist ja j&auml;relevalvet; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas policy-holders who, by virtue of the fact that they take the initiative in entering into a commitment in another State and thus place themselves under the protection of the legal system of that other State, do not require special protection in the State of the commitment, should be granted complete freedom to avail themselves of the widest possible market in life assurance and in the operations referred to in the First Directive; whereas other policy-holders should also be afforded adequate protection; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele, kes ei vaja kohustuse liikmesriigis erilist kaitset seet&otilde;ttu, et nad omal algatusel v&otilde;tavad kohustuse teises liikmesriigis ja asetavad end sellega teise liikmesriigi &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemi kaitse alla, tuleks anda t&auml;ielik vabadus kasutada v&otilde;imalikult laia elukindlustuse ja esimeses direktiivis nimetatud toimingute turgu; teistele kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele tuleks anda piisav kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in the management of some group pension funds, the multiplicity and complexity of the various schemes and their close connection with social security schemes call for careful study; whereas they should therefore be excluded from the scope of the provisions specific to freedom to provide services contained in this Directive; whereas they will form the subject matter of another Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> m&otilde;nede kollektiivpensionifondide haldamisel n&otilde;uab mitmesuguste kavade arvukus ja keerukus ning nende tihe side sotsiaalkindlustuskavadega hoolikat uurimist; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks need k&auml;esolevas direktiivis sisalduvate teenuste osutamise vabadusele omaste s&auml;tete reguleerimisalast v&auml;lja j&auml;tta; need moodustavad teise direktiivi sisu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the provisions in force in the Member States regarding contract law applicable to the activities referred to in the First Directive continue to differ; whereas the freedom to choose, as the law applicable to the contract, a law other than that of the State of the commitment may be granted in certain cases, in accordance with rules which take into account specific circumstances; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriikides kehtivad esimeses direktiivis nimetatud tegevuste suhtes kohaldatavad lepingu&otilde;igust k&auml;sitlevad s&auml;tted lahknevad j&auml;tkuvalt; teatavatel juhtudel v&otilde;ib vastavalt eeskirjadele konkreetseid olukordi arvestades anda vabaduse valida lepingu suhtes kohaldatavaks &otilde;iguseks &otilde;igus, mis pole kohustuse t&auml;itmise liikmesriigi &otilde;igus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the First Directive's provisions on transfer of portfolio should be reinforced and supplemented by provisions specifically concerning the transfer to another undertaking of the portfolio o contracts concluded by way of freedom to provide services; </inglise>
<eesti> esimese direktiivi s&auml;tteid kindlustusportfelli &uuml;leandmise kohta tuleks t&otilde;hustada ja t&auml;iendada s&auml;tetega, mis eriti k&auml;sitlevad teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel s&otilde;lmitud lepinguportfelli &uuml;leandmist teisele kindlustusseltsile; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the interests of protecting policy-holders, Member States should, at the present stage of the coordination process, be given the option of limiting the simultaneous pursuit of activity by way of freedom to provide services and activity by way of establishment; whereas no such limitation can be provided for where policy-holders do not require such protection; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustusv&otilde;tjate kaitse huvides peaks liikmesriikidele koosk&otilde;lastamisprotsessi praegusel etapil olema v&otilde;imalus piirata samaaegset tegelemist teenuste osutamise vabadusel p&otilde;hineva tegevuse ja asutamisel p&otilde;hineva tegevusega; sellist piirangut ei saa s&auml;testada juhul, kui kindlustusv&otilde;tjad sellist kaitset ei n&otilde;ua; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the taking-up and pursuit of activity by way of freedom to provide services should be subject to procedures guaranteeing the assurance undertaking's compliance with provisions regarding financial guarantees, conditions of assurance and premium rates; whereas those procedures may be relaxed where the activity pursued by way of freedom to provide services covers policy-holders who, by virtue of the characteristics of the commitment they propose to enter into, do not require special protection in the State of the commitment; </inglise>
<eesti> teenuste osutamise vabadusel p&otilde;hineva tegevuse alustamine ja j&auml;tkamine peaks s&otilde;ltuma korrast, mis tagaks elukindlustusseltsi vastavuse finantsgarantiisid, elukindlustustingimusi ja kindlustusmakseid k&auml;sitlevatele s&auml;tetele; seda korda v&otilde;ib l&otilde;dvendada, kui teenuste osutamise vabadusel p&otilde;hinev tegevus h&otilde;lmab kindlustusv&otilde;tjaid, kes kohustuse iseloomu t&otilde;ttu, mille nad kavatsevad v&otilde;tta, ei vaja kohustuse liikmesriigis erilist kaitset; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas for life assurance contracts entered into by way of the free provision of services the policy-holder should be given the opportunity of cancelling the contract within a period of between 14 and 30 days; </inglise>
<eesti> teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel s&otilde;lmitud elukindlustuslepingute puhul tuleks kindlustusv&otilde;tjale anda v&otilde;imalus lepingut 14-30 p&auml;eva pikkuse t&auml;htaja jooksul t&uuml;histada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the First Directive adopted the principle of prohibiting the simultaneous pursuit of the activities covered by Directive 73/239/EEC (1) (called the First Directive on the coordination of non-life insurance) as last amended by Directive 88/357/EEC (2) and those covered by the First Directive; whereas, while it authorized the continued existence of existing composite undertakings, it stated that they may not set up agencies or branches for life assurance; whereas the specific nature of the commitments entered into in the insurance field under the freedom of services regime nevertheless justifies, at least on a transitional basis as from notification of this Directive to Member States, the introduction of a degree of flexibility in the application of the above principle; </inglise>
<eesti> esimene direktiiv v&otilde;ttis vastu p&otilde;him&otilde;tte, mis keelab samaaegse tegelemise direktiiviga 73/239/EM&Uuml; (5) (mida nimetatakse esimeseks kahjukindlustuse koosk&otilde;lastamise direktiiviks), viimati muudetud direktiiviga 88/357/EM&Uuml; (6), reguleeritud tegevustega ja esimese direktiiviga reguleeritud tegevustega; lubades olemasolevate segakindlustusseltside j&auml;tkuvat olemasolu, n&auml;gi see ette, et need ei tohi asutada elukindlustust pakkuvaid esindusi v&otilde;i filiaale; teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel kindlustusvaldkonnas v&otilde;etud kohustuste erilise iseloomuga on siiski p&otilde;hjendatud kehtestada alates k&auml;esoleva direktiivi teatavakstegemisest v&auml;hemalt &uuml;leminekuajal liikmesriikidele nimetatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaldamisel teatav paindlikkus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas nothing in this Directive would prevent a composite undertaking from dividing itself into two undertakings, one active in the field of life assurance, the other in non-life insurance; whereas in order to allow such division to take place under the best possible conditions, it is desirable to permit Member States, in accordance with Community rules of competition law, to provide for appropriate tax arrangements, in particular with regard to the capital gains such division could entail; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei keela segakindlustusseltsil jagunemist kaheks kindlustusseltsiks, millest &uuml;ks tegeleks elukindlustuse, teine kahjukindlustuse valdkonnas; v&otilde;imaldamaks sellist jagunemist parimates v&otilde;imalikes tingimustes on soovitav lubada liikmesriikidel koosk&otilde;las &uuml;henduse konkurentsi&otilde;iguse eeskirjadega s&auml;testada sobivad maksukokkulepped, pidades eriti silmas sellise jagunemisega kaasnevaid v&otilde;imalikke kapitali kasvutulusid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to make provision for special cooperation in the sphere of freedom to provide services between the competent supervisory authorities of the Member States and between those authorities and the Commission; whereas provision should also be made for a system of penalties to apply where the undertaking providing the service fails to comply with the provisions of the Member State in which the service is provided; </inglise>
<eesti> vaja on s&auml;testada eriline teenuste osutamise vabaduse alane koost&ouml;&ouml; liikmesriikide p&auml;devate j&auml;relevalveasutuste ning nende asutuste ja komisjoni vahel; samuti tuleks ette n&auml;ha sanktsioonide s&uuml;steem, mida kohaldatakse, kui teenust osutav kindlustusselts ei j&auml;rgi teenuse osutamise liikmesriigi s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the technical reserves, including mathematical reserves, should be subject to the rules of and supervision by the Member State in which the service is provided where the provision of services involves commitments in respect of which the State in which the service is received wishes to provide special protection for policy-holders; whereas, however, if such concern to protect policy-holders is unjustified, the technical reserves, including mathematical reserves, should remain subject to the rules of and supervision by the Member State in which the undertaking is established; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustustehniliste eraldiste, sealhulgas matemaatiliste eraldiste suhtes peaks kohaldama teenuse osutamise liikmesriigi eeskirju ja j&auml;relevalvet, kui teenuste osutamine h&otilde;lmab kohustusi, mille osas teenuse saamise liikmesriik soovib kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele erilist kaitset pakkuda; kui selline kindlustusv&otilde;tjate kaitse pole p&otilde;hjendatud, kohaldatakse kindlustustehniliste eraldiste, kaasa arvatud kindlustusmatemaatiliste eraldiste suhtes kindlustusseltsi asukohaliikmesriigi eeskirju ja j&auml;relevalvet; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas some Member States do not subject life assurance contracts and the other operations covered by the First Directive to any form of indirect taxation, while others apply special taxes; whereas the structure and rate of those taxes vary considerably between the Member States in which they are applied; whereas it is desirable to avoid a situation where those differences lead to distortions of competition between undertakings in the various Member States; whereas, pending further harmonization, the application of the tax arrangements provided for by the Member State in which the commitment is entered into is a means of remedying such mischief; whereas it is for the Member States to establish a method of ensuring that such taxes are collected; </inglise>
<eesti> m&otilde;ned liikmesriigid ei kohalda elukindlustuslepingute ja muude esimeses direktiivis k&auml;sitletud toimingute suhtes &uuml;htki kaudse maksustamise liiki, teised aga kohaldavad erilisi makse; nende maksude struktuur ja m&auml;&auml;r lahknevad m&auml;rgatavalt liikmesriigiti, kus neid kohaldatakse; soovitav on v&auml;ltida olukorda, kus need lahknevused viivad eri liikmesriikide kindlustusseltside vahel konkurentsi moonutamiseni; edasise &uuml;htlustamiseni on sellise korratuse heastamise vahendiks kohustuse v&otilde;tmise liikmesriigi s&auml;testatud maksus&uuml;steemi kohaldamine; liikmesriigid peavad kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rama meetodi, millega tagatakse selliste maksude kogumine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the First Directive makes express provision for specific rules concerning the authorization of agencies and branches of undertakings whose head offices are outside the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> esimene direktiiv s&auml;testab selges&otilde;naliselt konkreetsed eeskirjad v&auml;ljaspool &uuml;hendust asuvate peakontoritega kindlustusseltside esindustele ja filiaalidele tegevusloa andmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made for a flexible procedure to make it possible to assess reciprocity with third countries on a Community basis; whereas the aim of this procedure is not to close the Community's financial markets but rather, as the Community intends to keep its financial markets open to the rest of the world, to improve the liberalization of the global financial markets in other third countries; whereas, to that end, this Directive provides for procedures for negotiating with third countries and, as a last resort, for the possibility of taking measures involving the suspension of new applications for authorization or the restriction of new authorizations; </inglise>
<eesti> s&auml;testada tuleks paindlik kord, mis v&otilde;imaldaks &uuml;henduse alusel hinnata kokkuleppeid kolmandate riikidega; selle protseduuri eesm&auml;rgiks ei ole sulgeda &uuml;henduse finantsturgusid, vaid vastupidi - kuna &uuml;hendus kavatseb hoida oma finantsturud &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud maailmale avatuna, siis on eesm&auml;rgiks &uuml;lemaailmsete finantsturgude liberaliseerimine kolmandates riikides; selleks s&auml;testab k&auml;esolev direktiiv kolmandate riikidega l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimise korra ja viimase v&otilde;imalusena meetmete v&otilde;tmise, mille hulka kuulub uute tegevusloa taotluste vastuv&otilde;tmise peatamine v&otilde;i uute tegevuslubade andmise piiramine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is desirable to take into account, within the meaning of Article 8c of the Treaty, the extent of the effort which needs to be made by certain economies showing differences in development; whereas, therefore, it is desirable to grant certain Member States transitional arrangements for the gradual application of the specific provisions of this Directive relating to freedom to provide services; </inglise>
<eesti> soovitav on asutamislepingu artikli 8c t&auml;henduses arvesse v&otilde;tta nende j&otilde;upingutuste ulatust, mida peavad tegema teatavad arengult erinevad rahvamajandused; seet&otilde;ttu on soovitav kehtestada teatavatele liikmesriikidele k&auml;esoleva direktiivi konkreetsete teenuste osutamise vabadust k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliseks kohaldamiseks &uuml;leminekukord; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the differences in the national legislations, it is also appropriate to grant to those Member States which so wish transitional arrangements enabling them to adapt their legislation before applying in their entirety, as regards group insurance contracts linked to a contract of employment or the intervention of a broker, the provisions of this Directive relating to the case where the policy-holder takes the initiative to conclude a contract by way of provision of services; </inglise>
<eesti> siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide lahknevusi silmas pidades on sobiv n&auml;ha ette liikmesriikidele, kes seda soovivad, &uuml;leminekukord, mis v&otilde;imaldab neil enne k&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tete kohaldamist kohandada oma &otilde;igusakte t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i vahendaja sekkumisega seotud grupikindlustuslepingute osas, mis k&auml;sitlevad juhtu, kui kindlustusv&otilde;tja algatab lepingu s&otilde;lmimise teenuste osutamise alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it will be particularly important to allow those Member States who so wish a sufficiently long period to be able to adopt the appropriate provisions in order to ensure the professional qualification and independence of insurance brokers; whereas taking into account the growing role such brokers play in advising those buying insurance and facing an increasing range of products as a result of the freedom to provide services, their professional qualification and independence will become essential elements for protection of the consumer, </inglise>
<eesti> eriti t&auml;htis on anda liikmesriikidele, kes seda soovivad, piisavalt aega sobivate s&auml;tete vastuv&otilde;tmiseks, et tagada kindlustusmaaklerite kutsekvalifikatsioon ja s&otilde;ltumatus; v&otilde;ttes arvesse selliste maaklerite kasvavat osa kindlustust ostvate ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse tulemusena laieneva tootevaliku ees seisvate isikute n&otilde;ustamisel, muutuvad nende kutsekvalifikatsioon ja s&otilde;ltumatus tarbijakaitsel &auml;&auml;rmiselt oluliseks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> TITLE I </inglise>
<eesti> I JAOTIS </eesti>
<inglise> General provisions </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The object of this Directive is to: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) supplement Directive 79/267/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&auml;iendada direktiivi 79/267/EM&Uuml;; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) lay down specific provisions relating to freedom to provide services in respect of the activities referred to in the said Directive, such provisions being set forth in Title III of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> b) n&auml;ha ette eris&auml;tted nimetatud direktiivis osutatud tegevuste alal teenuste osutamise vabaduse kohta, mis s&auml;testatakse k&auml;esoleva direktiivi III jaotises. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) "First Directive ": means Directive 79/267/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> a) esimene direktiiv - direktiiv 79/267/EM&Uuml;; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) "undertaking ": </inglise>
<eesti> b) kindlustusselts </eesti>
<inglise> - for the purposes of Titles I and II, means any undertaking which has received official authorization under Article 6 or Article 27 of the First Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> - I ja II jaotise kohaldamisel iga kindlustusselts, kes on saanud ametliku tegevusloa vastavalt esimese direktiivi artiklile 6 v&otilde;i artiklile 27, </eesti>
<inglise> - for the purposes of Titles III and IV, means any undertaking which has received official authorization under Article 6 of the First Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> - III ja IV jaotise kohaldamisel iga kindlustusselts, kes on saanud ametliku tegevusloa vastavalt esimese direktiivi artiklile 6; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) "establishment ": </inglise>
<eesti> c) &uuml;ksus - </eesti>
<inglise> means the head office, an agency or a branch of an undertaking, having regard to Article 3; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustusseltsi peakontor, esindus v&otilde;i filiaal, arvestades artiklit 3; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) "commitment ": </inglise>
<eesti> d) kohustus - </eesti>
<inglise> means a commitment represented by one of the kinds of insurance or operation referred to in Article 1 of the First Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> kohustus, mida v&auml;ljendab &uuml;ks esimese direktiivi artiklis 1 nimetatud kindlustusliikidest v&otilde;i -toimingutest; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) "Member State of the commitment ": </inglise>
<eesti> e) kohustuse liikmesriik - </eesti>
