<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the policy-holder is a natural person and has his habitual residence in a Member State other than that of which he is a national, the parties may choose the law of the Member State of which he is a national. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kindlustusv&otilde;tja on f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik ja tema alaline elukoht on teises liikmesriigis kui liikmesriik, mille kodanik ta on, v&otilde;ivad osapooled valida selle liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse, mille kindlustusv&otilde;tja ta on. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a State includes several territorial units, each of which has its own rules of law concerning contractual obligations, each unit shall be considered a country for the purposes of identifying the law applicable under this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui riik koosneb mitmest territoriaal&uuml;ksusest, millest iga&uuml;hes kehtivad lepinguliste kohustuste suhtes oma &otilde;igusnormid, loetakse iga territoriaal&uuml;ksust k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel kohaldatava &otilde;iguse kindlakstegemisel omaette riigiks. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State in which various territorial units have their own rules of law concerning contractual obligations shall not be bound to apply the provisions of this Directive to conflicts which arise between the laws of those units. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik, mille erinevatel territoriaal&uuml;ksustel on lepinguliste kohustuste suhtes oma &otilde;igusnormid, ei ole kohustatud kohaldama k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid nende territoriaal&uuml;ksuste &otilde;iguste vahel tekkivate konfliktide suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Nothing in this Article shall restrict the application of the rules of the law of the forum in a situation where they are mandatory, irrespective of the law otherwise applicable to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas artiklis ei kitsenda miski kohtu asukohariigi &otilde;iguse kohaldamist olukorras, kus see on kohustuslik, olenemata muidu lepingu suhtes kohaldatavast &otilde;igusest. </eesti>
<inglise> If the law of a Member State so stipulates, the mandatory rules of the law of the Member State of the commitment may be applied if and in so far as, under the law of that Member State, those rules must be applied whatever the law applicable to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigi &otilde;igus seda ette n&auml;eb, v&otilde;ib kohaldada kohustuse liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohustuslikke s&auml;tteid sel juhul ja niiv&otilde;rd, kui neid s&auml;tteid tuleb selle liikmesriigi &otilde;iguse kohaselt kohaldada, hoolimata lepingu suhtes kohaldatavast &otilde;igusest. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to the preceding paragraphs, the Member States shall apply to the assurance contracts referred to in this Directive their general rules of private international law concerning contractual obligations. </inglise>
