<inglise> Without prejudice to any subsequent harmonization, every assurance contract concluded by way of freedom to provide services shall be subject only to the indirect taxes and parafiscal charges on assurance premiums of the Member State of the commitment within the meaning of Article 2 (e) and, in the case of Spain, to the surcharges legally fixed to assist the Spanish body "Consorcio de Compensacion de Seguros' in its function of compensating for losses resulting form the occurrence of exceptional events in that Member State. </inglise>
